divs: sighting detailsi was driving west on i-20 west of the campus exit. i looked up and noticed a double z-shaped contrail. as i didn't want to be late going where i was going, i decided that there wasn't time to stop and take a picture. so, i took pictures through the windshield while driving. the enclosed picture was taken just past the i-35w off ramp. these contrails\clouds\whatever are becoming more frequent over texas. although, i have seen and photographed this type of formation before, i have never seen nor heard of two of them together.
